 special, temporary position that allows the holder to freely display the guild emblem, but does not give any other rights or privileges within the guild.  This was done to acknowledge those people who contributed to the guild emblem fund and thank them for their efforts, but still not slight those who are working their way towards Knighthood.  Giving them full Kngihthoods based on monetary contributions sets us down a path I think few of us would approve of.  Our Honorary Knights will still be expected to fulfill all of the normal requirements necessary to be promoted to full Knighthood, they just get to wear the emblem while doing so.  The officers felt this was a fair compromise.<br><br>NOTE:  Chances are good we missed someone’s name while we were collecting funds for the emblem.  Please do not take that as any sort of personal slight, it was simpya bit hectic at the time.  Just let one of the officers know, preferably whoever it was you gave the money to in the first place, and we’ll correct the situation as quickly as possible.<br><br>Squires and Keepers.  We have a large number of people at these ranks right now, hopefully we'll be able to promote a number fo them inthe next few weeks.  Because we did go through such a large influx of people in so short of a time frame we have set a few arbitrary dates as appropriate for review for promotion.  Anyone who joined the guild before October 29th will be eligible for promotion the first time on November 17th, and a second time (if appropriate) on December 16th.  Anyone who joined after October 29th will have their possible promotion dates set as in accordance with our admission guidelines.  This is not intended as a slight towards anyne, and I honestly don't believe we're going to have any problems promoting people as we go along.  Part of the reason we are using time designations is to prevent massive influxes of new members that may come with arbitrary promotions.<br><br>NOTE:  Those people invited into the guild before Oct. 29th will now be considered to be sponsored by the guild.  This will leave those people who did sponsor them initially free to sponsor another like-minded person.  I know we have a few more people waiting in the wings to get a sponsor, and with out current lack of Knights and such finding a sponsor for them will be difficult, if not impossible.<br><br>Class Leaders.  Most of these positions are filled but we’re very short on certain classes and thus don’t have a class leader to for them yet.  For the time being, I or one of the other officers will fill in those positions as best we can, we’re not going to leave those people needing to be promoted just hanging out there.  If you are interested in filling one of those positions, there are two things you can do.  1)  Ask about it.  We’ll let you know where we stand on the current situation and what you might want to do to get yourself ready and in the running for the position.  2)  Do your best.  If you’re consistently acting like a leader, chances are you’ll be approached about taking the position.<br><br>Promotions in general.  Here’s where things start to get a bit tricky.  Promotion from Squire to Keeper, and Keeper to Artisan/Knight are explained in the Admission Guidelines.  Going beyond that is largely left to the discretion of the officers already there.  Again, asking about a position will get you whatever information is available; acting like someone already in that position will probably get you an offer.<br><br>All that being said, here is our current roster with ranks within the guild.  I’ll get soe more information up here very soon in regards to what all of the ranks mean, and what their rights and responsibilities are.<br><!--EZCODE CODE START--><pre> Name            Class     Level     RankGwalchgwynn     Armsman       16     GuildleaderEdare           Armsman       21     Knight of the Black RoseJaret           Friar         18     Knight of the Black RoseAruth     